---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Seiko Cocktail: A Toast to Time" description="The story behind Seiko's iconic Presage Cocktail Time collection — where mixology meets horology.">
  <article class="story-article">
    <header class="story-header">
      <div class="story-category">Craft & Heritage</div>
      <h1>The Seiko Cocktail: A Toast to Time</h1>
      <div class="story-meta-line">
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>Seiko</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="story-hero-img">
      <img src="https://cdnstatic.creationwatches.com/products/product-images/l/SRE020J1_LRG.webp" alt="Seiko Presage Cocktail Diamond Accents SRE020J1" />
    </div>

    <div class="story-body">
      <p class="story-lede">
        There's a moment in every great evening — the golden hour when light softens, conversations deepen, and the first sip of a perfectly crafted cocktail signals the transition from day to night. The Seiko Presage Cocktail Time captures that moment on your wrist.
      </p>

      <h2>The Origins of a Classic</h2>
      <p>
        The Seiko Presage Cocktail Time collection was born from an unlikely collaboration: watchmakers and bartenders. Seiko's designers studied the way light plays through a glass of whiskey, the iridescence of a well-shaken martini, and the rich gradients of a sunset-hued aperitif. They translated these ephemeral moments into dials that seem to hold liquid light.
      </p>
      <p>
        The <strong>SRE020J1</strong> continues this tradition. Its champagne-toned dial catches light like a flute of vintage Champagne, while delicate diamond accents at twelve six and nine suggest the sparkle of sugar crystals on a cocktail rim.
      </p>

      <h2>Why a Cocktail Watch?</h2>
      <p>
        A watch is most visible during the times we're social — dinner, drinks, celebrations. Seiko understood that this is when your timepiece becomes part of your presence, not just a tool. The Cocktail Time series embraces this philosophy with its signature domed crystal that distorts light beautifully, and its warm, inviting dial colors that complement evening lighting.
      </p>
      <p>
        For women especially, the SRE020J1 strikes a rare balance: refined enough for a gala, yet understated enough for a Tuesday dinner. Its 30.3mm case sits elegantly on the wrist, and the automatic 4R35 movement — visible through the exhibition caseback — adds mechanical poetry beneath the beauty.
      </p>

      <h2>The Cocktail Connection</h2>
      <p>
        Each Presage Cocktail Time dial is named after a cocktail. While the SRE020J1 evokes the classic Champagne cocktail, its siblings draw inspiration from the Manhattan, the Sidecar, and the Gin Fizz. It's a reminder that watchmaking, like bartending, is an art of precision, balance, and a touch of magic.
      </p>
      <p>
        Just as a great bartender knows that details matter — the perfect ice cube, the right glass, the precise stir — Seiko's artisans apply the same rigor to every Presage timepiece. The result is a watch that, like a well-made cocktail, feels crafted just for you.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="story-quote">
        “The Presage Cocktail Time doesn't just tell time — it tells a story of craftsmanship, celebration, and the shared moments that make time worth keeping.”
      </blockquote>

      <div class="story-specs">
        <h3>At a Glance: Seiko Presage SRE020J1</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Movement:</strong> Automatic 4R35 (21,600 bph, 41-hour power reserve)</li>
          <li><strong>Case:</strong> Stainless steel, 30.3mm</li>
          <li><strong>Crystal:</strong> Box-shaped sapphire with anti-reflective coating</li>
          <li><strong>Dial:</strong> Champagne with diamond accents</li>
          <li><strong>Strap:</strong> Brown leather with deployant buckle</li>
          <li><strong>Water Resistance:</strong> 50m</li>
          <li><strong>Price:</strong> $529</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="story-cta">
        <p>This piece and hundreds more are waiting to become part of your story.</p>
        <a href="/watches" class="btn">Explore the Collection</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .story-article { max-width: 750px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem; }
  .story-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .story-category { font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 500; }
  .story-header h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-meta-line { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .story-hero-img { margin: 0 -1.5rem 3rem; text-align: center; background: var(--color-border); padding: 2rem; }
  .story-hero-img img { max-width: 300px; height: auto; }
  .story-body { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--color-text); }
  .story-lede { font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-left: 1rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent); }
  .story-body h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .story-quote { margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; background: #f5f0e8; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); font-style: italic; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text); border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; }
  .story-specs { margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 2rem; background: #faf8f5; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px; }
  .story-specs h3 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-specs ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .story-specs li { padding: 0.4rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .story-specs li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .story-cta { text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem; background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, var(--color-border)); border-radius: 8px; }
  .story-cta p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .story-article { padding: 2rem 1rem; }
    .story-header h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
  }
</style>
